item.dc:creator: @Nitor Nitor
item.description:
@Nitor wrote:

[quote=“final9999, post:72, topic:518969”][quote author=Nitor link=topic=637419.msg4432331#msg4432331 date=1403796770]
Although I wish to learn not “leech” as you people call it, After ending server.java with a ‘{’ I still receive an error mind explaining why?
[/quote]

You should end the class file with a closing bracket ‘}’ not the one u written ‘{’ (opening bracket). Other then that it could be the improts ur missing if ur not compiling with an IDE such as Eclipse or Netbeans.[/quote]

I should end the class file or the java file with a closing bracket? because class files are encryted java data that has been compiled.

And OP mentioned that the anti-leech could be fixed if you placed a ‘{’ at the end of server.java it already has a ‘}’ closing the file. So again I’m only trying to learn but its hard when you fix one problem but it created 15 others. And you mentioned that I should compile with Eclipse? I’ll give it a try but don’t see how that could fix the issue. Regardless I’ll come back after and let you know how the “Eclipse” thingy went.

EDIT: I found the real way to fix the Anti-Leech, you must end the } with a ;

Example:

[code]public static ObjectManager getObjectManager() {
return objectManager;

	};
}[/code]

OP didn’t mention that part.

EDIT: Now I fixed the client and re-uploaded the cache but now I have an error client sided “Connection error - retrying in 5…4…3…2…1…”

I’m assuming its an issue with the cache directory just not sure how to fix it. Any help?

EDIT: Fixed the cache downloading issue and the run directory’s that were missing.

Server is running smooth found a few bugs that with alittle help google should be easy to fix.

OP if you read this post can I have your permission to re-upload this source once I’ve fixed all the issues?
